Hundreds of mourners, including Springboks skipper Jean de Villiers, paid tribute to South Africa captain Senzo Meyiwa, who was shot dead on Sunday, during a moving memorial service in Johannesburg on Thursday.

The Standard Bank Arena was packed full as people united to pay tribute to Meyiwa and two other South African sports figures who died in the past few days. Former world champion 800-meter runner Mbulaeni Mulaudzi was killed in a car crash on Friday and female boxer Phindile Mwelase died on Saturday.

South Africa have been allowed to move their next African Cup of Nations qualifier to the hometown of the slain national team captain  as a tribute.

