South African Football Association President Danny Jordaan made the announcement at the memorial service  and also promised a statue of the goalkeeper would be built to stand outside SAFA's headquarters at Soccer City in Johannesburg.

The goalkeeper was shot and killed in an apparent house robbery on Sunday, unleashing dismay and anger in South Africa over the violent death of one of its most popular players.

Meyiwa had captained South Africa to the top of their qualifying group and was yet to concede a goal in qualifying, putting Bafana Bafana on the brink of sealing a place at next year's continental championship.

