'That statue will stand in front of SAFA House and when you walk into SAFA House, you must walk past Senzo,' Jordaan said.

Meyiwa had been in superb form for both club and country recently, leading Orlando Pirates to last season's African Champions League final, including a superb performance against TP Mazembe during which he saved two penalties. 

Since breaking into the national team last year, he claimed the No 1 spot in the absence of Itumeleng Khune, and was made captain in September.

